column5: Didn't know this was a thing.  http://www.cbc.ca/news/20k-in-lego-stolen-from-hamilton-toys-r-us-1.3326311
You really need to get here and go .
Lego is crazy expensive these days.   Also has high resale value as a result.  Not surprised there's a black market for it.
The parents buying Christmas presents at the flee market, supplied by the theft. Other than that... still a good month of open water out there. Musky doesn't close 'til the 15th of DECEMBER !

That's crazy..  I had a researcher at the archives the other day going on about investing in Legos rather than the stock market..  I'm starting to come around on this idea..  Seems you get more return for your buck, with way less risk!!
